<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1456,1779,2028]" box="[813,878,1779,1805]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">NOTE</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1456,1779,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
This species is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName authority="(C. K. Schneid.) G. Klotz. The" authorityName="G. Klotz. The" baseAuthorityName="C. K. Schneid." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis box="[1221,1330,1810,1837]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">C. kotschyi</emphasis>
(C. K. Schneid.) G. Klotz. The
</taxonomicName>
latter species is widely distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[1411,1455,1843,1869]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="RIEDL H." box="[822,941,1874,1900]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" pagination="13 - 26" refId="ref5495" refString="RIEDL H. 1969. - Cotoneaster Medik., in RECHINGER K. H. (ed.), Flora Iranica. Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz 66: 13 - 26." type="journal article" year="1969">Riedl 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="KHATAMSAZ M." box="[955,1135,1874,1900]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" pagination="209 - 239" refId="ref4690" refString="KHATAMSAZ M. 1992. - Cotoneaster Medik., in ASSADI M. (ed.), Flora of Iran. Research institute of forests and rangelands publication, Tehran 6: 209 - 239 [in Persian]." type="journal article" year="1992">Khatamsaz 1992</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName box="[1265,1381,1874,1900]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[1265,1381,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">C. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1028,1906,1932]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis box="[916,1028,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">C. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the small (up to 
<quantity box="[1250,1316,1906,1932]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
vs 
<quantity box="[1352,1455,1906,1932]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="6.0">6-14 mm</quantity>
in length) and orbicular leaves (vs elliptic-ovate) and the light red fruits (vs black- purple) (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1234,1970,1996]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[132,143,1986,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1389,215,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[198,1389,214,1802]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 3. — Cotoneaster minutus G.Klotz leaves and fruits outline (A) and close up (B). Collection number: Memariani &amp; Arjmandi 44626 (FUMH); determined by Raei Niaki &amp; Attar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573113/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Fig. 3A, B</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[841,973,2001,2027]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, Kashmir (
<bibRefCitation author="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B." box="[1093,1326,2001,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" refId="ref4629" refString="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B. 2009. - Cotoneasters: A Comprehensive Guide to Shrubs for Flowers, Fruit, and Foliage. Timber press, Portland, London, 344 p." type="book" year="2009">Fryer &amp; Hylmö 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1389,1437,2002,2028]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
